  "dateModified": "2026-01-01",
  "datePublished": "2026-01-01",
  "description": "Immutability is the property of data that cannot be modified after it is created. An immutable value is fixed at the moment of its creation; any operation that appears to \u0026ldquo;change\u0026rdquo; it instead produces a new value, leaving the original intact.\nIn contrast, mutable data can be altered in place. A mutable list allows elements to be added, removed, or replaced directly. An immutable list does not — appending an element produces a new list that contains all the original elements plus the new one, while the original list remains unchanged.\n",
  "name": "immutability",
